POLICE are appealing for witnesses after a two women were seriously assaulted in Edinburgh.
The 33-year-old and 22-year-old were attacked by a man and a woman on Springwell Place at around 11pm on Monday.
The older woman sustained various injuries to her head and body and required hospital treatment, while the younger woman sustained minor injuries to her head.
The first suspect is described as a white man of medium height and gaunt appearance while the woman had dark hair in a bun, a gaunt appearance, and an Edinburgh accent.
Anyone with information is encouraged to speak to Police by calling 101.
